# Per resources/regions/README.md: tile binaries and per-fetch provenance
# are never committed. region.toml is the only durable artifact per region.
# Hand-drawn .osm files (kind = "osm" overlays) are committed; everything
# under [[overlays]] kind = "hillshade" is gitignored (bake artefact).

# Basemap product + sidecar (per-product provenance per the
# field-deployment-package-shape sister-spike contract, extended in
# dev-log/2026-05-16-lidar-overlay-implementation.md).
**/basemap.pmtiles
**/basemap.provenance.json

# Hillshade overlay product + sidecar.
**/hillshade.pmtiles
**/hillshade.provenance.json

# Auto-fetched Overpass OSM overlay product + sidecar. The fetched file
# carries OpenStreetMap data verbatim (ODbL); per the bake-recipe shape
# we treat it as a derived product alongside basemap/hillshade and keep
# it out of git. The `[[overlays]] kind = "osm_overpass"` block in
# region.toml is the durable artefact.
**/osm-overpass.osm
**/osm-overpass.provenance.json

# Legacy single-file provenance shape (pre-2026-05-16-LIDAR migration);
# kept ignored so stale files don't surface in `git status` on machines
# that ran an older revision of fetch-region.ps1.
**/provenance.json

# Bake-time scratch.
**/provenance-mismatch.txt
**/*.pmtiles.tmp
